’Ł@c26d3ab0a0deac19195702edbd19b033c054d51af1f7e9e2cbdc7334934bc856ŁÜTitle: title: path type
Path: Examples
Content:
Show type of a filepath.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '.' | path type
dir

```
Show type of filepaths in a list.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ls | get name | path type


```
’Ł@22f85647af8e95a893623499f72c4fcc9711b24485becacf63c0cf8f20203841Ł Title: title: path type
Path: Notes
Content:
This checks the file system to confirm the path's object type.

If the path does not exist, null will be returned.
